<task id="001" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-01 Create `sprk_aipersona` Dataverse Entity (Pillar 1 foundation)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>002, 003, 004, 005</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, scope, schema, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Foundational schema change with downstream blocker impact (gates Pillar 1 endpoint, resolver, seed, agent factory wiring) + production Dataverse entity creation per Confirmation Trigger.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Foundation task; no other Phase A task touches Dataverse schema at this point.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the `sprk_aipersona` Dataverse entity — the 5th scope library entity introduced by R6 Pillar 1.
    This entity makes the chat-agent persona data-driven instead of hardcoded
    in `SprkChatAgentFactory.BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()`. Schema mirrors the existing 4
    scope entities (Actions / Skills / Knowledge / Tools) per Q2: SYS-/CUST- prefix
    enforcement, `parentScopeId` inheritance for most-specific-wins resolution per Q1,
    `description`, `systemPrompt` text field, `scopeType` (global / tenant / playbook-attached).

    Critical-path context: this task blocks (002) `GET /api/ai/scopes/personas` endpoint,
    (003) persona resolution methods in `IScopeResolverService`, (004) default SYS- persona
    seed row, and (005) agent factory wiring. The entire Pillar 1 deliverable chain depends
    on this entity landing first. The task itself ships ONLY the Dataverse schema —
    no BFF code changes here, so BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.

    Follow the existing `scope-architecture.md` pattern verbatim: same SYS-/CUST- ownership
    enforcement, same `parentScopeId` self-relationship for inheritance chains, same
    pagination/filter-friendly indexed columns as `sprk_analysisaction` etc. The Power Apps
    Dataverse forms (Q3) auto-generate from the entity definition — no custom form authoring
    in R6.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse engineer with Spaarke scope-library schema experience. Deep familiarity
    with `sprk_analysisaction` / `sprk_analysisskill` / `sprk_analysisknowledge` / `sprk_analysistool`
    entity patterns, Web API entity definitions, and PowerShell-driven schema deployment.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The `sprk_aipersona` entity exists in the Spaarke Dev Dataverse environment with all
    required fields, primary key strategy, indexes, self-referential `parentScopeId`
    relationship, and SYS-/CUST- prefix enforcement matching the existing 4 scope entities.
    The schema definition (XML or PS1 deployment script) is committed to the repo.
    Schema is verifiable via `pac` / Web API. All acceptance criteria green.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="scope-architecture-reference">docs/architecture/scope-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="scope-configuration-guide">docs/guides/SCOPE-CONFIGURATION-GUIDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-027">Follow unmanaged solution conventions for the new entity; logical name `sprk_aipersona`; publisher prefix `sprk_`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB for this task (no BFF code change). Report explicitly in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">No new feature flags introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-01">Schema MUST enforce SYS-/CUST- prefix on persona name + include `parentScopeId` self-relationship for inheritance + `description` + `systemPrompt` (text, multi-line) + `scopeType` option-set (global / tenant / playbook-attached).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-14">All scope CRUD operations honor SYS-/CUST- ownership boundary per `scope-architecture.md`. Persona entity follows the same enforcement model as the existing 4 scopes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project CLAUDE.md Pillar 1">Mirror the existing 4-scope schema verbatim. Do NOT invent a parallel schema.</constraint>
    <constraint source="Confirmation Trigger">Schema change to production Dataverse — pause for user confirmation before deploying to Spaarke Dev per project CLAUDE.md §Confirmation Triggers.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>dataverse/scope-entity-creation</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/entity-operations.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-create-schema/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/scope-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SCOPE-CONFIGURATION-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Scope entity schema canonical reference" location="existing `sprk_analysisaction` / `sprk_analysisskill` / `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse entities">
        Use these as the schema template. Copy field set: scope name (SYS-/CUST- prefix
        enforced), `parentScopeId` self-relationship (inheritance), `description`,
        `scopeType` option-set, audit fields. Replace action/skill-specific payload field
        with persona-specific `systemPrompt` (multi-line text, ~8KB max per NFR-10 budget).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="SYS-/CUST- prefix enforcement" location="docs/architecture/scope-architecture.md">
        Enforce via plugin (validate on create/update) or business rule. Follow the existing
        pattern used by the 4 production scope entities.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Check context usage. Output the mandatory declaration: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — Foundational schema change + downstream blocker for 4 Pillar 1 tasks". Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-01 + plan.md §4 Phase A.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` (if exists) and confirm task 001 status is 🔲, dependencies are empty. Update `current-task.md` to task 001.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read scope-architecture.md + SCOPE-CONFIGURATION-GUIDE.md in full. Inspect the 4 existing scope entity definitions (via `pac org list-tables` or Web API) to extract the canonical schema shape: field set, key strategy, self-relationship pattern, prefix enforcement mechanism.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Schema Definition">
      Create schema definition (XML for solution packaging OR PowerShell script using Web API per `dataverse-create-schema` skill). Fields: `sprk_name` (primary; enforces SYS-/CUST- prefix), `sprk_description` (text), `sprk_systemprompt` (multi-line text), `sprk_scopetype` (option-set: 1=Global, 2=Tenant, 3=PlaybookAttached), `sprk_parentscopeid` (self-lookup → `sprk_aipersona`), audit fields. Decide create approach: extend existing unmanaged solution OR sibling solution following ADR-027 conventions.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Prefix Enforcement">
      Implement SYS-/CUST- prefix enforcement (plugin OR business rule) mirroring the existing scope entities. Validate on create/update; reject names not starting with SYS- or CUST-.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="🛑 Confirmation Gate — Schema Deployment">
      PAUSE per project CLAUDE.md §Confirmation Triggers (schema change to production Dataverse entity). Present the schema definition to user and request approval to deploy to Spaarke Dev.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Deploy to Spaarke Dev">
      After confirmation: deploy via `dataverse-deploy` skill / `pac solution import`. Verify entity exists in Power Apps maker portal. Capture deployment evidence in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Smoke Test the Entity">
      Verify via Web API or `pac`: list `sprk_aipersona` entity metadata; confirm field definitions match the schema; confirm Power Apps auto-form is generated; attempt to create a placeholder row with name "SYS-TEST-PERSONA" (then delete) to confirm prefix enforcement allows valid prefix.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and confirm each is testable + passing. Record evidence per criterion in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the schema files (PS1 / XML). Run `adr-check` against same; verify ADR-027 (solution conventions), ADR-029 (BFF size — N/A 0 MB), ADR-018 (no new flags), spec NFR-14 (SYS-/CUST- enforcement). Both gates MUST pass before complete.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 001 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task (002). Note BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB. Report task completion + downstream unblock list.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="pac">Power Platform CLI — schema deployment + entity verification</tool>
    <tool name="az">Azure CLI — Key Vault for Web API credentials if needed</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit schema definition files on the R6 worktree branch</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-create-schema">Skill for Web API + PowerShell entity creation</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Skill for solution deployment to Spaarke Dev</tool>
    <tool name="mcp__dataverse__describe">MCP — verify entity metadata after deployment</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="schema">solutions/{solution}/Entities/sprk_aipersona/Entity.xml OR scripts/Create-AiPersonaEntity.ps1 (NEW)</output>
    <output type="schema">prefix-enforcement plugin OR business rule (NEW)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status: 001 🔲 → ✅)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/current-task.md (reset to next task)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-001-schema-evidence.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_aipersona` entity exists in Spaarke Dev and is visible via Power Apps maker portal.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Schema fields match canonical: `sprk_name` (primary, SYS-/CUST- enforced), `sprk_description`, `sprk_systemprompt` (multi-line text), `sprk_scopetype` (option-set with 3 values), `sprk_parentscopeid` (self-lookup), audit fields.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SYS-/CUST- prefix enforcement rejects an entity row with name "INVALID-PERSONA" and accepts "SYS-DEFAULT" / "CUST-ACME-LEGAL".</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Self-referential `parentScopeId` relationship supports inheritance chain queries (Web API navigation works).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Power Apps auto-generates a working form for the new entity (Q3 compliance — no custom UI needed).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Schema definition committed to repo follows ADR-027 unmanaged solution conventions.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code changed; recorded in task notes).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Downstream tasks (002, 003, 004, 005) unblocked — TASK-INDEX updated.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
